// A block used directly as a pipeline stage (not a function body) infers its
// &0 type from the upstream stage's stdout. Here parseInt produces an Int, so
// `&0` inside the block is an Int and the arithmetic is integer arithmetic.
// `&0` is a consuming read, so the single input is bound once and reused.

echo "3" | parseInt | { const n = &0; yield n * n }
